rComments: Near incomprehensible and seemed incapable of lecturing in chronological order. His logic seemed to go in circles. TA was useless (he was doing his masters in French history for god sakes). Very disappointed and my mark suffered for it.

professor dudley is a really, the course isnt too difficult, and the tests are fair but he has the most horrible lecturing style; completely incomprehensible and has nothing to do with the stuff in the textbook

Professor Dudley was a great Professor as he was extremely insightful and was available to answer questions in class or during his office hours. To those who have negative things to say about him I know you did not go to his office hours or engage him in discussion during or after class. All the best to you Prof Dudley! Regards,Christopher Linhares

I think people here are treating him more harshly than he deserves.  He does sometimes tends to drag discussions on.  However, he really seems to care and if you approach him for help, you get it.  As long as you put time into the course, you'll be ok.

He wasn't so bad he was interesting. Although he really needs to organize his lecture a little better.  It was really hard to take notes but if you could just sit and listen a not have to barf it up later for an exam it would have been really cool.
